715833f-a.text:
West 227th Street, west from Van Corlear Place (left) to Adrian Ave., showing W.P.A. employees engaged in a road repair project.

May 8, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
715833f-a.folder: 227th Street (West) & Van Corlear Place, Manhattan, NY

723690f-a.text:
Van Corlear Place, north from Jacobus Place to West 227th Street, as photographed to show pavement conditions. These photos are progressive. In the last appears a modern apartment bldg. on the north side of 227th Street. The grade
there slopes down to Marble Hill Avenue
May 3, 1937
1-2-3
W. P. A., photo
Five Boroughs Project

(This is actually West 227th Street looking west from Van Corlear Avenue to Adrian Avenue.  The apartment house is on Andrian Avenue.)
